benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: POST /1.0/kb/bundles/{bundleId}/tags - Add tags to bundle

covered: Valid Payload: Comprehensive coverage for valid tag additions, including single and multiple tags and edge-case empty payload (TC01, TC02, TC03, TC04, TC05, TC07).
Invalid Payload: Coverage for malformed JSON, non-array body, invalid/unknown UUIDs, extra fields, and malicious payload (TC10, TC11, TC12, TC15, TC18).
Missing/Invalid Headers: Handling of missing X-Killbill-CreatedBy header and missing request body (TC13, TC14).
BundleId validation: 400 for invalid format and 400 for non-existent bundle (TC08, TC09).
Payload size boundaries: 201 for max payload (TC20) and 400 for payload too large (TC21).
Deduplication: Ensuring no duplicate Tag objects in response (TC26).
Integration tests: POST followed by GET verification (TC27) and cross-service data consistency (TC28).
Performance/Resilience: 201 under normal load (TC24) and peak load with concurrency (TC25); 503 service unavailable (TC17), 504 timeout (TC22); transient network recovery (TC19).
gaps: Rate limiting / throttling not covered (no explicit burst-load tests).
Caching headers / caching behavior not tested for POST responses (ETag/Cache-Control).
403 Forbidden scenarios not explicitly tested (only 401 covered).
Edge-case validations beyond presence (e.g., invalid header values) not exhaustively tested.
Higher-scale concurrency stress beyond TC25 not covered.
recommendations: Add rate-limiting tests to validate throttling and error handling under high load.
Add tests to verify caching headers and idempotency considerations on POST responses.
Broaden authorization coverage to include 403 Forbidden cases and invalid/expired tokens.
Enhance concurrency tests to simulate higher-than-TC25 load and assess stability.
Test header value validity and case-insensitivity (e.g., mixed-case header names).
